WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:03.147
Your app runs while you're connected.

00:00:03.147 --> 00:00:05.652
Production means it runs when you're gone.

00:00:05.652 --> 00:00:06.726
Three short steps,

00:00:06.726 --> 00:00:08.158
all from your laptop.

00:00:08.928 --> 00:00:10.042
Here's the difference.

00:00:10.042 --> 00:00:12.642
In development you start the app from

00:00:12.642 --> 00:00:14.500
inside the repo over SSH.

00:00:14.500 --> 00:00:15.614
Close the session,

00:00:15.614 --> 00:00:17.843
and the app dies with it.

00:00:17.843 --> 00:00:20.443
In production you launch it detached from

00:00:20.443 --> 00:00:21.186
your laptop:

00:00:21.186 --> 00:00:23.043
the server owns the process,

00:00:23.043 --> 00:00:24.157
your connection doesn't.

00:00:27.517 --> 00:00:29.677
Time to start the app in production mode from the

00:00:29.677 --> 00:00:32.317
laptop. The deploy command calls

00:00:32.317 --> 00:00:35.437
the same up function we used during development, but

00:00:35.437 --> 00:00:38.237
it runs detached. Close your laptop

00:00:38.317 --> 00:00:39.677
and the app keeps going.

00:00:42.623 --> 00:00:45.183
App running in production. Same command, same

00:00:45.183 --> 00:00:46.783
result, on the real server.

00:00:50.206 --> 00:00:53.246
Now enable autostart so the app survives

00:00:53.246 --> 00:00:55.886
a server reboot. From here on, if the

00:00:55.886 --> 00:00:58.606
server restarts, this repo comes back

00:00:58.686 --> 00:00:59.406
automatically.

00:01:01.860 --> 00:01:04.900
Autostart on. The app survives reboots.

00:01:08.416 --> 00:01:11.056
Let us list which repositories have autostart

00:01:11.056 --> 00:01:13.696
enabled. Confirms our app is in the boot list.

00:01:17.132 --> 00:01:18.812
There it is, in the boot list.

00:01:22.203 --> 00:01:24.923
And to stop the app, one command from the laptop

00:01:25.163 --> 00:01:27.803
. One command up, one command down. All

00:01:27.803 --> 00:01:28.683
from your terminal.

00:01:31.730 --> 00:01:33.730
Stopped. One command up, one command down.

00:01:34.708 --> 00:01:37.748
And that's production mode in a nutshell. See

00:01:37.748 --> 00:01:38.628
you in the next one!
